<p>At the risk of sounding dumb by using jargon, I&#8217;d like to refute comment #1 by pointing out that the original proposition &#8216;smart people see the world as uncomplicated&#8217; (p->q) says nothing about its inverse statement &#8216;stupid people see the world as complicated&#8217; (~p->~q).</p>

