<p>Nope, I actually think it usually follows a hill pattern. It initially seems simple. Then, with a little bit of knowledge, it seems complicated (since you don&#8217;t really understand it). Then once you understand it really well, it seems simple again.</p>

<p>My answer to the specific question of education is the subject of the book chapter i&#8217;m currently working on, so I hope you&#8217;ll excuse me if I don&#8217;t get into it here.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>The mental gymnastics necessary to work out quantum physics is staggering.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Well, yes, doing hard math is hard. But that&#8217;s different from it being complicated. I&#8217;m talking about conceptual understanding, not the actual work involved in applying it.</p>

